http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/National-conference/article14013329.ece

Karnataka Communal Harmony Forum, central committee, is organising ‘The sea of co-existence’, a national conference on co-existence, where different religions, castes, ideologies, cultures, and languages converge, on January 30. The conference, to be held at Town Hall in Mangaluru, between 9 a.m. and 8 p.m., features Yakshagana, drama, musical presentation of Sufi vachana, songs of struggle, Daff Qawwali and other forms of expression that show India’s secular social fabric. Swaraj Abhiyan leader Yogendra Yadav, human rights activist Teesta Setalvad, and writers Baragur Ramachandrappa and Chandrashekar Patil are among those expected to participate.